        "content": "<p>lukewagner opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13690\">issue #13690</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Based on <a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/component-model/pull/647\">CM/#647</a>, there are already traps for sync {stream,future}.{read,write} if the stream/future is already in a waitable sets, but this PR also added traps for {stream,future}.cancel-{read,write} and subtask.cancel which seem to be necessary for the same reason.  <a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/component-model/blob/main/test/async/trap-if-sync-and-waitable-set.wast\"><code>test/async/trap-if-sync-and-waitable-set.wast</code></a> I believe tests this (failing when it hits an <code>unreachable</code> instead of the intended trap).</p>\n</blockquote>",
